# Question 1 - Linux Environment Verification

## Command 1
$ mkdir -p ~/CLI-Graded-Assignment/Q1
$ cd ~/CLI-Graded-Assignment/Q1

Explanation: Created the Q1 working directory and moved into it.

## Command 2
$ id
uid=1000(coder) gid=1000(coder) groups=1000(coder),27(sudo)

Explanation: Displayed the user identity. The UID and GID are 1000 (coder), and the user belongs to the coder and sudo groups.

## Command 3
$ groups
coder sudo

Explanation: Listed the group memberships of the current user: coder and sudo.

## Command 4
$ echo $SHELL
/bin/bash

Explanation: Showed the currently active shell, which is /bin/bash.

## Command 5
$ pwd
/home/coder/CLI-Graded-Assignment/Q1

Explanation: Printed the absolute path of the current working directory.

## Command 6
$ ls -la
total 1
drwxr-xr-x 2 coder coder 2 Jun 23 11:31 .
drwxr-xr-x 3 coder coder 3 Jun 23 11:31 ..

Explanation: Listed all files including hidden ones in long format. The folder was newly created, so it only contained the . and .. entries.

